    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <pre class="highlight"><code>
date_default_timezone_set('America/Los_Angeles');
$now = new Zend_Date('2008-05-10 20:09:25', Zend_Date::ISO_8601);
echo $now . "\n";
$broke = clone $now;
$broke-&gt;addMonth(1);
echo $broke;
</code></pre>

<p>Result
May 10, 2008 8:09:25 PM
Jun 1, 2008 8:09:25 PM</p>

<p>Expected Result
May 10, 2008 8:09:25 PM
Jun 10, 2008 8:09:25 PM</p>

<p>Adding Zend_Date::setOptions(array('extend_month' =&gt; true)); fixes this problem for me.  But, I would prefer to use the SQL method for adding months and not the spreadsheet style.</p>

